  "prompt": "What are some good engineering colleges in Pune?",
  "response": "Pune is home to several reputed engineering colleges. Here are some of the top ones:\n\n1. **Indian Institute of Science Education and Research (IISER) Pune**\n   - Known for its strong focus on research and education in science and engineering.\n\n2. **College of Engineering, Pune (COEP)**\n   - One of the oldest and most prestigious engineering colleges in India, offering a wide range of undergraduate and postgraduate programs.\n\n3. **Pune Institute of Computer Technology (PICT)**\n   - Highly regarded for its computer science and information technology programs.\n\n4. **Army Institute of Technology (AIT)**\n   - Known for its quality education and disciplined environment, primarily catering to wards of army personnel.\n\n5. **MIT World Peace University (MIT-WPU)**\n   - Offers a variety of engineering programs with a focus on holistic development.\n\n6. **Vishwakarma Institute of Technology (VIT) Pune**\n   - Known for its strong academic programs and good placement records.\n\n7. **Bharati Vidyapeeth College of Engineering (BVCOE)**\n   - Offers a range of engineering courses and is known for its good infrastructure and faculty.\n\n8. **Symbiosis Institute of Technology (SIT)**\n   - Part of the Symbiosis International University, known for its multidisciplinary approach and strong industry connections.\n\nThese colleges are known for their academic excellence, infrastructure, faculty, and placement opportunities. It's advisable to research further based on specific courses, entrance exams, and your personal preferences.",
